history.content:
The EECS degree program leaves plenty of room to complete all the requirements. I would avoid a fourth class with that schedule. CS61C is a heavy project based course which has been getting harder over the semesters. CS70 has consistently challenging weekly problem sets. R1B also may have either a decent amount of reading or essays. Those three classes alone will keep you very busy, but manageable.

**

I did 61c, 70, 120 and did well and found it doable, although very challenging. I was a little burnt out by the end of the semester though, and there were weeks with 2 midterms and projects which were pretty tough, but overall I thought it was doable.
